In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter, sugars and vanilla. Beat in egg. Add cocoa and milk. Combine flour and baking powder; fold into creamed mixture with walnuts and chocolate chips. Roll teaspoonfuls of dough into balls; place 2 in. apart on ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 350 degrees F for 10-12 minutes. Cool for 5 minutes before removing to wire racks to cool.